name: TXHARKZHU 772.9
description:
TXHARKZHU 772.9 is the first of a series of portalizers. Small cyber representations of specific fluxes of birth, development and death of unkown elements. Fusioned togheter they appear as subjects of a sequence of specific energetic measurements, captured in a moment.

772.9 is the nearest star to an isolated communicative galaxy. It coitains mineral traces of organic parasyting the dead matter.
